---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Mouadh Bekhouche, Laravel/PHP backend developer and PhD researcher building Nexus Scholar and research workflow tools.">
  <article class="article">
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Mouadh Bekhouche</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Laravel/PHP backend developer and PhD researcher working on research workflow infrastructure,
        Nexus Scholar, and plant-disease AI with evidence-first public boundaries.
      </p>
    </header>
    <div class="article-content">
      <h2>Current Direction</h2>
      <p>
        My current public work centers on senior Laravel/PHP backend engineering and research software
        infrastructure. The flagship surface is Nexus Scholar, a Laravel/PHP ecosystem for systematic
        literature review workflows.
      </p>
      <h2>What I Build</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Laravel/PHP backend systems, APIs, package boundaries, and SaaS-style applications.</li>
        <li>Research workflow tools for scholarly search, screening, deduplication, citation graphs, and exports.</li>
        <li>Evidence-aware project documentation that separates verified work from roadmap or research planning.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Public Boundary</h2>
      <p>
        Reusable tooling, documentation, and verified evidence can be public. Unpublished thesis methods,
        private roadmap details, credentials, client data, and sensitive research planning stay controlled.
      </p>
      <h2>Links</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar">Nexus Scholar on GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/mbsoft31">Personal developer GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mouadhbekhouche/">LinkedIn</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

